AUSTRALIAN OPEN
February 10, 2021
Pablo Carreno Busta
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
  P. CARRENO BUSTA/J. Vesely
 6-3, 7-6, 2-6, 6-4
 THE MODERATOR:   Questions, please.
 Q. Good match today.  Can you just take us through what happened out there.
 PABLO CARRENO BUSTA:   Yeah, it was a really tough match, no?  Jiri plays really good, serving unbelievable, and giving not very much.  It was not easy to be focused all the time on do my things.
 Of course in the first set it was easier.  The conditions at the beginning of the match I think was better for me with the sun.  The ball bounce more than at the end of the match.  When it start the night it was tougher to me from the baseline.  And he was serve, he continue serving all the time 210, 215, and making a lot of aces.
 But when I have three breakpoints and I made two, so when I have the opportunity, I take it and was very important to win the match.
   
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT